#Question 5 Question 5: Enter each coloumn as a vector in R, and collect these into a cingla data frame. Name the hydrogen peroxide column ‘Peroxide’ and the fungal growth rate colomn ‘Growth.rate’.

hydrogen=c(0.27,0.21,0.34,0.32,0.24,0.29,0.18,0.20,0.29)
fungal=c(1.79,1.01,1.71,1.89,1.41,1.15,1.13,1.20,1.10)
my.data=data.frame("Peroxide"=hydrogen,"Growth.rate"=fungal)

#Question 6 Question 6: Create a scatter plot of fungal growth rate versus peroxide concentration from the newly created data frame. Make sure to label the plot properly (lable the axes and make sure to provide the measurement units.

plot(my.data$Peroxide,my.data$Growth.rate,xlab="Hydrogen Peroxide Concentration (umoles/gm)",ylab="Fungal Growth Rate (cm/day)")

#Question 7 Question 7: How does the growth rate of the fungus change with increasing levels of hydrogen peroxide, and does this agree or disagree with the hypothesis?

With increasing levels of hydrogen peroxide the scatter plot shows an increase in the fungal growth rate in leaf tissue, therefore, this does not agree with the hypothesis.
